Admin → GRANT → User gets access

Admin → REVOKE → User loses access

==========

GRANT and REVOKE in Simple Words

Think of a database like a classroom.

Teacher = Database Admin
Students = Database Users
Permissions = What users are allowed to do
1. GRANT
Meaning

GRANT means:

✅ "Give permission"

Real-Life Example

Teacher says:

"You can read this book."

That is like:

GRANT SELECT
ON students
TO user1;
What User Can Do?
Permission	Meaning
SELECT	View data
INSERT	Add new data
UPDATE	Change data
DELETE	Remove data
Example
Query
GRANT SELECT
ON students
TO 'student1'@'localhost';
Simple Meaning

User student1 can now:

✅ View data from students table

❌ Cannot add or delete data

Before GRANT
User	Access
student1	No access
After GRANT
User	Access
student1	Can view table
2. REVOKE
Meaning

REVOKE means:

❌ "Take back permission"

Real-Life Example

Teacher says:

"Now you cannot read this book."

That is like:

REVOKE SELECT
ON students
FROM user1;
Example
Query

REVOKE SELECT
ON students
FROM 'student1'@'localhost';

Simple Meaning

User student1:

❌ Cannot view data anymore

Before REVOKE
User	Access
student1	Can view table
After REVOKE
User	Access
student1	No access
Easy Memory Trick

========

| Command | Meaning           |
| ------- | ----------------- |
| GRANT   | Give permission   |
| REVOKE  | Remove permission |


